narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: USAF 101 is recommended for students in ROTC
I would recommend this course to students interested or participating Air Force ROTC or plan on joining the military, but it is certainly a niche class.

This class is more for AFROTC cadets than for a typical Yale student, but anyone can take the class. The workload is definitely manageable and reasonable, and topics covered in the class are meaningful to those of us looking to learn about the Air Force in general.
This class prepares you with relevant information to a career in the Air Force and educates you on what you will need to know in your career. It is directly applicable to real life.
